@startuml
title ITIR / SensibLaw - System Context

left to right direction

actor User
actor Advocate
actor Lawyer
actor Clinician
actor Caseworker

rectangle "External Institutions" as EXT {
  component "Landlord / Agent"
  component "Church / Institution"
  component "Health Service"
  component "Welfare Provider"
  component "Tribunal / Court"
}

rectangle "ITIR / SensibLaw" as SYS

User --> SYS : narrative, evidence, goals
Advocate --> SYS : case support
Lawyer --> SYS : legal review
Clinician --> SYS : clinical documents
Caseworker --> SYS : welfare records

SYS --> User : guidance, actions, timeline, reports
SYS --> Advocate : structured case outputs
SYS --> Lawyer : evidence packet, duty matrix
SYS --> Clinician : continuity / contradiction summary
SYS --> Caseworker : unmet need / obligation map

SYS ..> EXT : references rules, obligations,\nprovider actions, outcomes

note bottom of SYS
  Plain-language read:
  case material comes in, gets normalized into evidence and graphs, then
  turns into obligations, outputs, and audit trails under governance.
end note
@enduml

